		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Activation of the CD28 surface receptor provides a major costimulatory signal for T cell activation resulting in enhanced production of interleukin-2 ( IL-2 ) and cell proliferation . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In primary T lymphocytes we show",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "that CD28 ligation leads to the rapid intracellular formation of reactive oxygen intermediates ( ROIs ) which are required for CD28-mediated activation of the NF-kappa B/CD28-responsive complex and IL-2 expression . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Delineation of the CD28 signaling cascade was found to involve protein tyrosine kinase activity ,",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "followed by the activation of phospholipase A2 and 5-lipoxygenase . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Our data suggest",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "that lipoxygenase metabolites activate ROI formation which then induce IL-2 expression via NF-kappa B activation . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "These findings should be useful for therapeutic strategies and the development of immunosuppressants targeting the CD28 costimulatory pathway . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}